7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Pipedream and Pipefy share a solid foundation of core features including Visual Builder, Api Connections, Scheduling, Conditional Logic. Where Pipedream pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Code Support, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Pipefy uniquely offers Ai Actions, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Pipedream holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Pipefy scores 7/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Pipedream and Pipefy offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Pipedream's free tier and Pipefy's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
