b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Pipedream is best suited for developers, API integrations, technical teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Pipefy, meanwhile, shines for HR teams, procurement, service management, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2018, Pipedream describes itself as \"Connect APIs with code-level control and serverless execution.\" Pipefy, established in 2014, positions itself as \"AI-enhanced business process automation with customizable workflows.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Pipedream** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Pipefy is a poor choice — far from it. Pipefy excels in its own right, particularly for HR teams and procurement.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value full code support with node.js and python, go with Pipedream. If excellent pipe/kanban workflow model matters more to you, Pipefy is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
